TITLE: ONE NIGHT AT THE C.G. MUSEUM
During World War II, an enigmatic opportunity arrived unexpectedly for the women of America. Over ten thousand young women, drawn from elite women’s colleges and small Southern towns alike, were recruited by the U.S. Army and Navy to serve as codebreakers.
They would go on to make history.
You are here to learn about these women’s stories – and it is your job to ensure history does not change tonight.

Some enigmatic rogues have been scheming as of late to not only steal from the prestigious Museum, but besmirch its displays and placards too, the night before the Annual Exhibition. 

With full security all around in the shadows, there are three people scouting the Museum tonight – including you.

Meet the Characters:

Detective Meyer Driscoll | Game-Mode: Cipher decrypting

Decrypt the 5 strange messages left by the Enigmatic Rogues. What are they trying to communicate? Can you trace their steps and find out where they are going next? Let’s try to catch them in time.

Difficulty: Medium

Museum Curator Helen Aderholt | Game-Mode: Trivia, Multiple choice

Walk through the corridors and restore the 5 placards that have been left distorted. You may not have any access to external resources for cross-checking, but you have one brilliant thing the Enigmatic Rogues can’t take from you: Your mind!

Difficulty: Easy

Hacker PURPLE_CIPHER | Game-Mode: Cipher & Trivia, no hints

To catch the Enigmatic Rogues, you must first think like them. Since you’re operating from the Museum’s security room, your resources and time alike are rather limited. Thankfully, you need the 3 remaining puzzle pieces to both track down the Enigmatic Rogues and restore the Museum’s information placards in one blow.

Difficulty: Advanced

*For beginners, Detective or Curator is recommended! 
*For risk-takers, they may try out Hacker!


